headline: Russia's former liberal elite adopts the Kremlin's anti-European rhetoric
description: Silenced since the start of the war in Ukraine, former Russian liberals have hardened their rhetoric following the collapse of ceasefire negotiations. Once critical of the Kremlin, they now blame Europe, accusing it of fueling the ongoing war.

headline: The art of being Oscar Wilde's grandson
description: As Ireland prepares to mark the 125th anniversary of Oscar Wilde's death, Merlin Holland, his only living descendant, works in France to protect the memory of a man who was long viewed as scandalous.

headline: Paris restaurants with a New York attitude
description: The French capital has recently seen a wave of New York-style restaurants spring up, from slice shops to delis and red sauce joints. Parisians are flocking to these spots to savor not only a slice of culinary culture but also the enduring myth of the Big Apple.

headline: Why our old clothes end up in the UAE
description: The country has emerged as a leader in sorting secondhand clothing, taking advantage of Europe's inability to process its own stockpiles. This outsourcing comes with clear environmental and social costs.

headline: Inside the archives of shoemaker Roger Vivier
description: This star shoemaker of the 1930s through the 1990s spent his long career experimenting with all kinds of designs. His archives, a testament to his boundless creativity, are now housed in a Parisian hôtel particulier.
